default1.1.default&#xa0; 
defaultCIHT welcomes the recognition of 
defaultthe importance of 
defaultcertainty of investment and reform to the Highways Agency.  
default1.2.default&#xa0; 
defaultThe current proposals to be enacted in legislation within this Parliamentary cycle offer a pragmatic and deliverable approach to change.  More 
defaultradical changes
default, for example the introduction of a Regulated Utility Model in conjunction with direct user charging,
default to the management of the network may have the capacity for greater improvements in the longer term and it is good that such options have be
defaulten considered in Action for Roads.
default1.3.default&#xa0; 
defaultCertainty of investment over a sustained period is important if overall improvements to the network are to be delivered effectively and efficiently. This need for certainty applies both to the reformed Highways Agency and
default other “client” bodies and the wider supply chain of organisations working in the sector. 
default1.4.default&#xa0; 
defaultThe five year funding period set out (in the Road Investment Strategy) is a welcome improvement from annualised budget cycles.  However, this falls short of the peri
defaultods required to undertake a holistic approach to asset management and delivery of customer expectations.  
default1.5.default&#xa0; 
defaultExperience from other models and schemes, for example on the M25 D
defaultesign Build Finance &amp; Operate
default scheme, and PFI investments in the local highway sect
defaultor have delivered real benefits through considering needs over a 25 year period.  Such approaches have enabled ambitious investment programmes to be delivered over a five year period followed by managed, longer operational periods. This 'invest to save' ap
defaultproach helps reduce ongoing operational costs through upfront investment in the asset. 
default1.6.default&#xa0; 
defaultCertainty of investment over a sustained period will also allow a more resilient network to be developed, allowing the reformed Highways Agency and its supply chain to 
defaultmeet the potential challenges of climate change by taking a longer term view of the needs of the network.
default 
default1.7.default&#xa0; 
defaultThe increased level of investment is also welcomed as the sector has faced budget reductions that have led to asset deterioration.
default The investment ide
defaultntified will enable a series of key benefits to be delivered such as improving capacity, reducing congestion and improving reliability. These benefits will improve the network for users and deliver environmental benefits
default..
default1.8.default&#xa0; 
defaultThe sector already has a lot of e
defaultxperience to build on.  For instance, the lessons learnt from the managed motorways programme already underway have demonstrated the ability of the sector to deliver additional capacity withi
defaultn existing highway corridors. These improvements have been delive
defaultred more efficiently than full motorway improvements, delivering benefits to users and the environment in a shorter timescale.
default1.9.default&#xa0; 
defaultFuture Investment strategies should be informed by linking an understanding of the assets required to deliver all the purposes of
default the network derived from customer need. A proposed approach is set out in our response to Question 3 below.
default1.10.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCertainty of investment and clarity of the pipeline of works anticipated is fundamental to the ability of the supply chain to deliver a significant
default programme of investment in the timescales set out. If certainty is not delivered then 
defaultproviding 
defaultincreased resource will have a time lag before benefits can be 
defaultfully 
defaultdelivered.
default1.11.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is welcome that the importance of the local road network is recognised by Ac
defaulttion for Roads and that the effects on non-vehicular highway users are addressed to some degree. 
default1.12.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultNearly all journeys on the strategic road network begin and end on the local highway network. Unless linked to consideration of wider effects, improvements to
default the strategic road network (SRN) may have significant effects upon the local road network affecting all highway users, local communities and the environment. These effects may occur through diversion onto unsuitable parts of the network by charging, conge
defaultstion or control of access to the SRN. Customers do not take a different view of the networks they travel 
defaulton,
default a consistent appropriate standard of service delivery needs to be the aim.
